The paper deals with matching scholarly documents against a reference dataset, which involves information retrieval, string similarity, and supervised methods. These techniques are commonly used in fields such as information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
